{"_record_type": "fragment", "type": "expert_knowledge", "content": "unction:: flake8.utils.is_using_stdin\n\nAnother helpful function that is named only to be explicit given it is a very\ntrivial check, this checks if the user specified ``-`` in their arguments to\n|Flake8| to indicate we should read from stdin.\n\n.. autofunction:: flake8.utils.fnmatch\n\nThe standard library's :func:`fnmatch.fnmatch` is excellent at deciding if a\nfilename matches a single pattern. In our use case, however, we typically have\na list of patterns and want to know if the filename matches any of them. This\nfunction abstracts that logic away with a little extra logic.\n", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T14:04:01.077191", "embedding": [0.44594916701316833, -0.04044897109270096, -3.1098484992980957, -1.9853838682174683, 0.9840344786643982, -1.419136643409729, 0.7420368790626526, 0.10746215283870697, -0.8252018094062805, -1.255038857460022, -0.9083037972450256, 0.3818175792694092, 1.9510782957077026, 0.38086119294166565, -0.6212723851203918, -0.3100730776786804, 0.11850371956825256, -1.5024372339248657, 0.6477594375610352, -0.30299749970436096, -0.5976831316947937, 0.1496298462152481, -0.5975891351699829, 0.2680216431617737, 1.2163991928100586, -0.037177227437496185, -0.18035730719566345, 0.41637447476387024, -1.3769385814666748, 0.13662061095237732, 1.7548118829727173, 0.1270194798707962, 0.241092249751091, -0.60820072889328, -1.5702301263809204, -0.6785512566566467, 1.1299521923065186, 0.3379853367805481, 0.019854474812746048, 0.2701602280139923, 0.4332647919654846, 0.9236985445022583, -0.3944963812828064, 0.1781030297279358, 0.7452250123023987, 0.23708243668079376, 0.538987934589386, 0.4401654303073883, 0.5606154203414917, -1.3847692012786865, 0.2519869804382324, -0.40274858474731445, 0.13432039320468903, -0.14097808301448822, 1.460278868675232, 0.5655097365379333, 1.162636160850525, 1.1821191310882568, 0.12379679828882217, 0.4768059253692627, 0.0069303191266953945, 0.913162112236023, -0.69